history.content: I can only speak for 100, but no, you won't be required to be in Lab 10X if you want to be in Discussion 10X. What has happened the last few semesters is we send out some sort of preference form before the semester starts and pair you to a discussion and lab (no guarantee that this will happen again next semester, but it's likely).

can anyone let me know if these 3 classes force you to sign up in pairs i.e. Discussion 108B and Lab 108C, or do you get to take whatever time works for discussion and whatever time works for lab?  (I'm not talking about the registration, I know they all use 999)

I'll assume all 3 of these classes have online signups for discussions and labs in August?  Or can I just walk into any discussion? I'm guessing that because there are labs in all 3 of these classes, there must be some signup of some sort?
history.subject: 61B, 61C, C100 discussion/lab pairs
